cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.CY, cs.SE

The paper discusses the use of Internet-connected wearables for telemonitoring and diagnosis in the healthcare domain, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also focuses on security aspects in client layer, fog layer, and cloud layer, which is related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of fog computing for processing data near the body sensor network is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the management of health data using fog devices, which is related to data management and analysis (cs.CY). Finally, the paper proposes a service-oriented edge computing architecture, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
